Installation instructions for Sitar
=====================================

PREREQUISITES:

	Linux (Sitar was tested on Ubuntu 12:04)
	gcc >= version 4.5
	python >= version 2.7
	scons
	openMp (optional) Required for parallel simulation.
		

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS (FOR LINUX):

	STEP 1. Run install.py 
		(This should generate an executable "sitar_translator" 
		inside ./translator/parser folder)


	STEP 2. Add the following lines to your ~/.bashrc file
	   to use the sitar translator and compiler executables
	   outside the installation folder. Replace <path> 
	   with absolute path of sitarV2.0 folder

		#-------------------------
		#sitarV2 paths:
		export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=<path-to-sitar>/translator/antlr3Cruntime/build/lib:${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}
		export PATH=<path-to-sitar>/scripts:${PATH}
		alias antlrwors='java -jar <path-to-sitar>/translator/antlrworks-1.4.3.jar'
		#-------------------------

	STEP 3. Refer to /examples/README for running examples.


	STEP 4. (optional) for enabling syntax highlighting inside 
	Vim editor for sitar language, refer to vim/README


	
